{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "FastJX",
    "description": "Fast-JX UV photolysis rates (main model, src/Fast-JX.jl:1276). 0-D component computing 13 J-rates (j_H2O2, j_H2COa, j_H2COb, j_O3, j_O31D, j_o32OH, j_NO2, j_NO3a, j_NO3b, j_N2O5, j_CH3OOH, j_ActAld, j_PAN) from atmospheric state (lat, lon, t_utc, T, P, H2O). Computes the cosine of the solar zenith angle inline using the NOAA Spencer-Fourier formula (same as lib/solar.esm Solar.cos_zenith), then calls the flux_interp_1..18 registered functions for the 18-band tropospheric actinic flux bilinear lookup. Cross-section (\u03c3_X) and quantum-yield (\u03d5_O31D) interpolation use interp.linear over T. The O(1D) photolysis adjustment (adjust_j_o31D) accounts for quenching by H2O, H2, N2, O2.\n\nMigration from esm-lnl6 (polecat/esm-lnl6). Registered function calls resolved:\n  cos_solar_zenith_angle \u2192 inlined as NOAA Spencer-Fourier AST (gt-p3ep resolved)\n  flux_interp_1..18      \u2192 registered_functions/flux_interp_{1..18}.esm (esm-9vcj)\n  calc_direct_flux       \u2192 registered_functions/calc_direct_flux.esm (esm-hlrp; not used in j-rate computation \u2014 exposed as registered function for caller use)\n  calc_direct_fluxes     \u2192 registered_functions/calc_direct_fluxes.esm (esm-2u1x; same note)\n\nCompared to FastJX_interpolation_troposphere (fastjx_interp_troposphere.esm):\n  - cos_sza is computed internally from lat/lon/t_utc (not a parameter)\n  - F_i uses registered function calls (fn: flux_interp_i) rather than inline tables\n  - \u03c3, \u03d5, j-rate, and O(1D) adjustment computations are identical",
    "authors": [
      "GasChem.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-lnl6)"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-22T00:00:00Z",
    "tags": [
      "chemistry",
      "photolysis",
      "fast-jx",
      "registered-function-calls",
      "interp-linear",
      "interp-bilinear",
      "noaa-spencer-fourier"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "Neu, J.L., Prather, M.J., and Penner, J.E. (2007), Global atmospheric chemistry: Integrating over fractional cloud cover, J. Geophys. Res., 112, D11306."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Wild, O., Zhu, X., and Prather, M.J. (2000), Fast-J: Accurate Simulation of In- and Below-Cloud Photolysis in Tropospheric Chemical Models. J. Atmos. Chem., 37(3), 245\u2013282."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Burkholder, J.B. et al. (2015), Chemical Kinetics and Photochemical Data for Use in Atmospheric Studies, Evaluation No. 18, JPL Publication 15-10."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Spencer, J.W., 1971. Fourier series representation of the position of the sun. Search 2(5), 172."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Source: GasChem.jl/src/Fast-JX.jl + src/interpolations_FastJX.jl (commit 8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309)."
      }
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "FastJX": {
      "coupletype": "FastJX",
      "variables": {
        "lat": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "deg",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Observer latitude in degrees north of the equator. Range [-90, 90]. Input to cos_solar_zenith_angle."
        },
        "lon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "deg",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Observer longitude in degrees east of the prime meridian. Range [-180, 180]. Input to cos_solar_zenith_angle."
        },
        "t_utc": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "s",
          "default": 1782043200.0,
          "description": "UTC time as seconds since the Unix epoch. Default: 2026-06-21 12:00:00 UTC (noon at summer solstice, reference test scenario)."
        },
        "T": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "K",
          "default": 298.0,
          "description": "Air temperature (K). Drives \u03c3_X(T) and \u03d5_O31D(T) and adjust_j_o31D."
        },
        "P": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 101325.0,
          "description": "Air pressure (Pa). One axis of the bilinear actinic-flux interpolation; also feeds adjust_j_o31D."
        },
        "H2O": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "ppb",
          "default": 450.0,
          "description": "Water vapor mixing ratio (ppb). Feeds adjust_j_o31D."
        },
        "day_of_year": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Day of year of t_utc, 1..366. Extracted from the UTC calendar date.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "fn",
            "name": "datetime.day_of_year",
            "args": [
              "t_utc"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hour": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "UTC hour of t_utc, 0..23.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "fn",
            "name": "datetime.hour",
            "args": [
              "t_utc"
            ]
          }
        },
        "minute": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "UTC minute of t_utc, 0..59.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "fn",
            "name": "datetime.minute",
            "args": [
              "t_utc"
            ]
          }
        },
        "second": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "UTC second of t_utc, 0..59.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "fn",
            "name": "datetime.second",
            "args": [
              "t_utc"
            ]
          }
        },
        "gamma": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "rad",
          "description": "NOAA fractional-year angle \u03b3 = 0.01721420632103996 \u00b7 ((day_of_year - 1) + (hour - 12)/24). Same formula as lib/solar.esm Solar.cos_zenith.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "*",
            "args": [
              0.01721420632103996,
              {
                "op": "+",
                "args": [
                  {
                    "op": "-",
                    "args": [
                      "day_of_year",
                      1.0
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "op": "/",
                    "args": [
                      {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                          "hour",
                          12.0
                        ]
                      },
                      24.0
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "solar_declination": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "rad",
          "description": "Solar declination \u03b4 (radians) \u2014 Spencer (1971) 6-term Fourier series in \u03b3.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "+",
            "args": [
              0.006918,
              {
                "op": "*",
